    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e00005f158f",
      "text": "In Chapter 1, we saw the [cycle of learning]. In Chapter 2, we learned about the [driving force] for the cycle. ",
      "created": 1549189945,
      "updated": 1549190041,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e00005f1590",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549190041,
      "updated": 1549190041,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e00005f1591",
      "text": "By turning the cycle, do you keep going around the same place, or do you climb little by little like a [spiral staircase]?",
      "created": 1549189945,
      "updated": 1549190045,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e00005f1592",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1549189945,
      "updated": 1549190048,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e00005f1593",
      "text": "It depends on whether knowledge obtained by one cycle accumulates or not. In this chapter, we learn about the accumulation of what we learned, in other words, the [memory].",
      "created": 1549189945,
      "updated": 1549190074,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b38aff09e00005f1594",
      "text": "",
